    <div class="INFO">
      <h4>
        INFO => :
      </h4>
      <div class="tb"> 
        x2-init is created as a modern and portable initialization system for gnu operating systems on the linux kernel.Putting safety , speed of operation and ease of use in the first place .Development is conducted primarily under slackware GNU/linux, there will also be support for Devuan and Arch
        <br/> +--------------------------+<br/>
        the initialization system is based on SysVinit, but the latter is already obsolete
        <br/>     
      </div>
      <h4>
        Components of x2-init  => :
      </h4>
      <div class="tb"> 
        1 - classic init system <br/>
        2 - init-shell <br/>
        3 - x2init units(  replacement of classic scripts from BSD)<br/>
        +--------------------------+<br/> 
        <i> For install rc.d base </i> <br/>
        $ cd ../cfg-def-s/ && sh install.sh <br/> 
        OTHER TUTORIALS IN THE TAB "GUIDES"
		<br/>
        +--------------------------+<br/> 
        Release 1.0 avaibale !!!	<br/> 
		:) BÐ¯ANCHES/RElEASES= <br/>
		"main" is untested roling branch ,"1.0_untested" is tested stable release ,"1.1_release" in october 2024 (maybe!). 
		<br/> 
	  </div>
